01:34:58,600 --> 01:35:00,840
 - So in our today's class,

1628
01:35:00,840 --> 01:35:03,920
 we started with the discussion of machine learning.

1629
01:35:03,920 --> 01:35:06,680
 We discussed machine learning is a branch of AI,

1630
01:35:06,680 --> 01:35:08,440
 which performs various action

1631
01:35:08,440 --> 01:35:10,980
 without explicitly being programmed.

1632
01:35:10,980 --> 01:35:14,180
 We discussed about supervised and unsupervised learning.

1633
01:35:14,180 --> 01:35:17,400
 Supervised is where we have an idea of the label,

1634
01:35:17,400 --> 01:35:22,180
 unsupervised where we don't know what we going to do.

1635
01:35:22,180 --> 01:35:24,420
 In supervised, we have classification

1636
01:35:24,420 --> 01:35:27,360
 where the type of the attribute is categorical

1637
01:35:27,360 --> 01:35:30,040
 and regression where the type of the attribute

1638
01:35:30,040 --> 01:35:32,200
 is of type continuous.

1639
01:35:32,200 --> 01:35:33,640
 In unsupervised learning,

1640
01:35:33,640 --> 01:35:36,200
 we have clustering where you just analyze your data

1641
01:35:36,200 --> 01:35:37,440
 and based on that analysis,

1642
01:35:37,440 --> 01:35:39,720
 you group your data into various clusters.

1643
01:35:39,720 --> 01:35:42,600
 You have unsemi-supervised learning.

1644
01:35:42,600 --> 01:35:44,680
 We discussed about outlier analysis.

1645
01:35:44,680 --> 01:35:48,080
 We discussed about association analysis.

1646
01:35:48,080 --> 01:35:50,440
 And then further to that one,

1647
01:35:50,440 --> 01:35:55,440
 we discussed about the machine learning algorithm,

1648
01:35:55,480 --> 01:35:57,460
 machine learning model as well.

1649
01:35:57,460 --> 01:36:01,320
 Then we also discussed about the Chris DM architecture.

1650
01:36:01,320 --> 01:36:05,080
 We discussed that there are six different phases

1651
01:36:05,080 --> 01:36:07,340
 of Chris DM architecture.

1652
01:36:07,340 --> 01:36:10,600
 We discussed that the first stage is where you will

1653
01:36:10,600 --> 01:36:14,960
 understand your business understanding.

1654
01:36:14,960 --> 01:36:18,040
 You will understand what are your business objective.

1655
01:36:18,040 --> 01:36:19,840
 You will assess your situation.

1656
01:36:19,840 --> 01:36:22,940
 What do you have in order to accomplish

1657
01:36:22,940 --> 01:36:24,440
 that particular task?

1658
01:36:24,440 --> 01:36:26,800
 We will also set our data mining goals.

1659
01:36:26,800 --> 01:36:29,680
 We discussed data mining is a process

1660
01:36:29,680 --> 01:36:31,520
 to extract the interesting patterns

1661
01:36:31,520 --> 01:36:33,600
 from the huge amount of data.

1662
01:36:33,600 --> 01:36:35,920
 Then we discussed about the data understanding

1663
01:36:35,920 --> 01:36:38,200
 where you will collect your initial data,

1664
01:36:38,200 --> 01:36:40,880
 you will analyze it, you will visualize it,

1665
01:36:40,880 --> 01:36:42,560
 and you will verify its quality

1666
01:36:42,560 --> 01:36:45,560
 if there will be any problem, any issue in your data.

1667
01:36:45,560 --> 01:36:48,400
 Do your data has any outliers?

1668
01:36:48,400 --> 01:36:52,560
 Does it have any missing values and so on?

1669
01:36:52,560 --> 01:36:55,200
 Then whatever the problems you have done here,

1670
01:36:55,200 --> 01:36:57,540
 you will actually fix those one into third stage

1671
01:36:57,540 --> 01:37:00,260
 of data preparation, where you will select your data,

1672
01:37:00,260 --> 01:37:02,080
 clean your data from the missing values,

1673
01:37:02,080 --> 01:37:03,920
 outline analysis and so on.

1674
01:37:03,920 --> 01:37:06,760
 And you will also construct some new features

1675
01:37:06,760 --> 01:37:09,400
 or maybe you can integrate some of the features.

1676
01:37:09,400 --> 01:37:11,140
 You will permit your data properly.

1677
01:37:11,140 --> 01:37:13,980
 And then in the modeling stage, which is the fourth stage,

1678
01:37:13,980 --> 01:37:15,840
 you will apply certain models

1679
01:37:15,840 --> 01:37:19,640
 and then you will do all that analysis.

1680
01:37:19,640 --> 01:37:22,280
 After that analysis, you will evaluate it

1681
01:37:22,280 --> 01:37:25,280
 and you will also assess whether you have met the target,

1682
01:37:25,280 --> 01:37:26,440
 whichever you have done

1683
01:37:26,440 --> 01:37:30,360
 in your first business understanding stage,

1684
01:37:30,360 --> 01:37:32,080
 whether you have met those targets

1685
01:37:32,080 --> 01:37:35,400
 and then for the deployment for the three assessments,

1686
01:37:35,400 --> 01:37:37,080
 we are not gonna deploy your model

1687
01:37:37,080 --> 01:37:38,840
 rather than we're gonna mention

1688
01:37:38,840 --> 01:37:41,280
 all of the lesson learns here.

1689
01:37:41,280 --> 01:37:43,160
 What was the problem that you observed?

1690
01:37:43,160 --> 01:37:44,800
 What was the problem in your data set?

1691
01:37:44,800 --> 01:37:47,780
 What was the problem in your machine learning models?

1692
01:37:47,780 --> 01:37:50,480
 How you can improve it, how you can make it better,

1693
